name: The Holy Virgin of Nazareth
description: For more than 200 years, the Nazaré candle procession is celebrated on the second Sunday of October in Belém do Pará. There are more than 2 million faithful on the streets of the capital. The greatest expression of faith in Catholicism in the world. Requests are made and graces are taken that lead pilgrims to accompany the processions, which are 7 in 48 hours. Twiter <@Belaamazonia>; Instagram <catarinagomesxx>.
